New Records: Zach Edey became the first rookie in NBA history with at least 20 points and 10 rebounds while hitting at least 90% of his shots.
Key Match Events: Zach Edey finished the game with 25 points, 12 rebounds, four blocks and one steal, hitting 11-of-12 shots, including 1-for-1 from deep.
Post-Match Reflections: Fans are ready to crown Zach Edey as the ROY winner after one great game.
Zach Edey will have to outplay every rookie from the 2024 draft class to earn the Rookie of the Year honor.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Zach Edey had a 3-pointer in the third quarter that stunned the crowd inside the Barclays Center.
Zach Edey has proven to be a willing shooter from behind the arc, doubling his triple attempts from college to the NBA.
